<gp_project_root ver="1"> <gallery> <tool name="SummarizeNearby" type="script" toolboxalias="analysis" gallery_group="Summarize Data"> <displayname>Summarize Nearby</displayname> <description>Finds features that are within a specified distance of features in the input layer and calculates statistics for the nearby features. Distance can be measured as a straight-line distance, a drive-time distance (for example, within 10 minutes), or a drive distance (within 5 kilometers). Drive-time and drive distance measurements require that you are logged in to an ArcGIS Online organizational account with Network Analysis privileges, and they consume credits.</description> </tool> <tool name="SummarizeWithin" type="script" toolboxalias="analysis" gallery_group="Summarize Data"> <displayname>Summarize Within</displayname> <description>Overlays a polygon layer with another layer to summarize the number of points, length of the lines, or area of the polygons within each polygon, and calculate attribute field statistics about those features within the polygons.</description> </tool> <tool name="Statistics" type="function" toolboxalias="analysis" gallery_group="Summarize Data"> <displayname>Summary Statistics</displayname> <description>Calculates summary statistics for field(s) in a table.</description> </tool> <tool name="Enrich" type="function" toolboxalias="analysis" gallery_group="Enrich Data"> <displayname>Enrich</displayname> <description>Enriches data by adding demographic and landscape facts about the people and places that surround or are inside data locations.
